result.name: Uncle Padak

reviews.text: Really friendly service and very decent Korean fried chicken as well as the delicious kimchi fried rice. The spicy padak chicken was good but not that spicy, whilst the soy sauce chicken was tasty. Place is pretty cozy and wasn't too busy on a Tuesday night. Reservations are possible.

I absolutely love this place. The large Padak with red sauce plus on the side kimchi, corn, egg rolls and, if you're really hungry, ramen. So good! Service is quick. Asahi on tap! And K-pop videos on the screen. Great place for an informal dinner. Five stars - if you like KFC (Korean Fried Chicken) :-)
Tastes good and look styling

Probably one of the best Korean Fried Chicken places I have been to and I have lived in Korea. If you are confused as to what to order you can always mix and match by ordering half one style and the other half another style to maximize the taste. 

The place gets busy quickly so get there early. They do reservations so call ahead. A great place.

Small place for Korean fried chicken, they have a simple menu and staffs were friendly. Ordered the spring onion boneless fried chicken. Their fried chicken was piping hot, not greasy at all and came with rice dumplings, gyozas and it was in a portion bigger than expected, 1 chicken is enough for 2 adults to share. Received discounts from eatigo, it was such a great deal. We brought baby along, they dont offer booster or baby chair but arranged bench seating so it was a pleasant dining experience.
